<subSubSection id="C34CD2DFFFF7FFFDFCD3AE52DF66F86D" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98154FFF7FFFDFCD3AE52DB63F8CB" blockId="6.[833,1472,1150,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFCD3AE52DD89FB08" bold="true" box="[833,956,1150,1174]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Remarks. â€“</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7FCA5FFF7FFFDFC52AE52DA79FB0B" author="Harry, H" box="[960,1100,1150,1173]" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" pagination="121 - 158" refId="ref8049" refString="Harry, H. W., 1985. Synopsis of the supraspecific classification of living oysters (Bivalvia: Gryphaeidae and Ostreidae). The Veliger, 28: 121 - 158." type="journal article" year="1985">Harry (1985)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFAD0AE52DB8DFB0B" authorityName="Harry" authorityYear="1985" box="[1346,1464,1150,1173]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Planostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFAD0AE52DB8DFB0B" box="[1346,1464,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Planostrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, exclusively for 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFC60AEB2DA91FB2B" authorityName="Hanley" authorityYear="1846" box="[1010,1188,1182,1205]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pestigris">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFC60AEB2DA91FB2B" box="[1010,1188,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Ostrea pestigris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This genus is described as of moderate size (to 
<quantity id="4CAE2CB1FFF7FFFDFBF7AE92DA88FB4B" box="[1125,1213,1214,1237]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" unit="mm" value="75.0">75 mm</quantity>
), very compressed in one plane, being non-lamellose and with a continuous outer shell layer. Well-developed chomata line up along the dorsal margins near the hinge, with a wide and flat marginal commissural shelf and a lavender outer surface with radial stripes. This species can be distinguished easily from other oysters because of the consistent shape of a smooth, flattened, circular disc. Unlike other oysters, it is usually free from encrustations and the influence of the substratum to which it is attached. This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFBECAFD2DBB9F98B" box="[1150,1420,1534,1557]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="densellamellosa">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFBECAFD2DBB9F98B" box="[1150,1420,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Ostrea densellamellosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFCD3AC32DA77F9AB" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[833,1090,1566,1589]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Alectryonella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="plicatula">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFCD3AC32DA77F9AB" box="[833,1090,1566,1589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Alectryonella plicatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a smooth and straight shell margin. The latter two have crenulated shell margins. It is also different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFBF2AC72DB04F9EB" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[1120,1329,1630,1653]" class="Bivalvia" family="Gryphaeidae" genus="Hyotissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="numisma">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFBF2AC72DB04F9EB" box="[1120,1329,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Hyotissa numisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a white interior instead of a violet one and in lacking the vesicular microstructure of gryphaeids. This species has been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFBC0AC92DB8EF94B" authority="Crosse, 1869" authorityName="Crosse" authorityYear="1869" box="[1106,1467,1726,1749]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="paulucciae">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFBC0AC92DB28F94B" box="[1106,1309,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Ostrea paulucciae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7FCA5FFF7FFFDFAB5AC92DB8EF94B" author="Crosse, H" box="[1319,1467,1726,1749]" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" pagination="183 - 188" refId="ref7641" refString="Crosse, H., 1869. Diagnoses molluscorum novorum. Journal de Conchyliologie, 17 (3 e serie, Tome 9): 183 - 188." type="journal article" year="1869">Crosse, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFCE4ACF2DACFF96B" authority="Sowerby, 1871" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1871" box="[886,1274,1758,1781]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="palmipes">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFCE4ACF2DA02F96B" box="[886,1079,1758,1781]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Ostrea palmipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7FCA5FFF7FFFDFBD6ACF2DACFF96B" author="Sowerby, G" box="[1092,1274,1758,1781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" refId="ref9218" refString="Sowerby, G. B., 1871. Conchologia Iconica. Volume 18. Ostrea. L. Reeve &amp; Co, London." type="book" year="1871">Sowerby, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, on the basis of similar shell characters (Tchang &amp; Lou, 1956). Therefore, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFCF9AD32DDC5F8AB" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1871" box="[875,1008,1822,1845]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="palmipes">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFCF9AD32DDC5F8AB" box="[875,1008,1822,1845]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">O. palmipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F341C1C4FFF7FFFDFBA5AD32DAAEF8AB" box="[1079,1179,1822,1845]" name="Malaysia" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
as identified by Morris &amp; Purchon (1981) is actually 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FAD7FFF7FFFDFBE3AD12DB7BF8CB" baseAuthorityName="Hanley" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1137,1358,1854,1877]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Planostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pestigris">
<emphasis id="B9225D46FFF7FFFDFBE3AD12DB7BF8CB" box="[1137,1358,1854,1877]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="487">Planostrea pestigris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
